VALUES
(44, 4, 2, 43, 11, 47, 48, 'preached through Jesus the resurrection', 'Concern Over Jesus'' Influence', 'Both passages emphasize the fear of Jesus'' growing influence. In Acts, the apostles preach the resurrection, which grieves the leaders, while in John, the council fears that belief in Jesus will lead to loss of power and control.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 2, 45, 8, 11, 11, 'resurrection from the dead', 'Resurrection and Spiritual Life', 'This connection highlights the theme of resurrection in both passages. Acts 4:2 mentions the resurrection from the dead, while Romans 8:11 speaks of being quickened through the Spirit that raised Jesus.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 2, 46, 15, 23, 23, 'resurrection from the dead', 'Resurrection and Christ''s Coming', 'This connection highlights the theme of resurrection, as both passages address the resurrection through Jesus and its implications for believers. Acts 4:2 mentions the resurrection from the dead, while 1 Corinthians 15:23 speaks of those who belong to Christ at his coming, linking the two concepts.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 3, 44, 5, 18, 18, 'laid hands on them', 'Apostles Imprisonment Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the act of laying hands on the apostles and their subsequent imprisonment. This connection highlights the continuity of opposition faced by the apostles in their ministry.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 3, 40, 10, 16, 17, 'put them in hold', 'Persecution of the Apostles', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of persecution faced by believers. Acts 4:3 describes the apostles being imprisoned, while Matthew 10:17 warns of being delivered up to councils.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 3, 44, 16, 19, 24, 'put them in hold', 'Imprisonment of Apostles', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of imprisonment of the apostles for their teachings. In Acts 4:3, the apostles are put in hold, while in Acts 16:24, Paul and Silas are cast into prison.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 3, 42, 22, 52, 52, 'laid hands on them, and put them in hold', 'Arrest and Detainment Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the act of detainment, with Acts 4:3 describing the apostles being held overnight and Luke 22:52 referencing Jesus being confronted by authorities. This connection highlights the theme of authority figures apprehending individuals for their beliefs.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 3, 43, 18, 12, 12, 'laid hands on them', 'Arrest and Binding of Figures', 'Both passages emphasize the act of binding individuals during a time of arrest. In Acts, the apostles are held overnight, while in John, Jesus is bound by the authorities.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 4, 44, 2, 41, 41, NULL, 'Growth of Early Church', 'Both passages emphasize the significant number of believers added to the early church, with Acts 2:41 noting about three thousand souls and Acts 4:4 reporting about five thousand men. This connection highlights the rapid expansion of the Christian community following the apostles'' preaching.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 4, 47, 2, 14, 17, 'believed', 'Connection of Belief and Triumph', 'Both passages emphasize the impact of belief in Christ, with Acts noting the growth of believers and 2 Corinthians highlighting the triumph in Christ. This connection highlights the transformative power of faith as it leads to salvation and spiritual influence.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 4, 55, 2, 9, 10, NULL, 'Connection of Belief and Endurance', 'This connection highlights the theme of belief in the word of God leading to salvation. Both passages emphasize the importance of enduring challenges for the sake of those who believe, as seen in the growth of believers in Acts and the apostolic endurance in 2 Timothy.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 4, 50, 1, 12, 18, NULL, 'Connection of Gospel Advancement', 'Both passages emphasize the furtherance of the gospel despite challenges. Acts 4:4 highlights the growth of believers, while Philippians 1:12-18 shows how adversity can inspire boldness in preaching.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 4, 44, 28, 24, 24, NULL, 'Belief and Rejection Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the response to the word spoken, highlighting belief and disbelief. Acts 4:4 notes a significant number of believers, while Acts 28:24 presents a division between those who believed and those who did not.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 4, 1, 49, 10, 10, NULL, 'Gathering of the People', 'This connection highlights the theme of gathering, as seen in both passages. Acts 4:4 mentions a significant number of believers, while Genesis 49:10 speaks of the gathering of people to Shiloh.', 'theme', 0.307, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 4, 23, 45, 24, 24, 'believed', 'Belief and Righteousness Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of belief in the Lord leading to righteousness and strength. Both passages emphasize that those who come to the Lord will find support and affirmation.', 'theme', 0.307, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 5, 44, 4, 8, 8, 'rulers, and elders', 'Connection of Rulers and Elders', 'This connection highlights the presence of the rulers and elders in both passages. The mention of ''rulers'' and ''elders'' in Acts 4:5 is echoed in Acts 4:8, emphasizing their role in the narrative.', 'keyword', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 5, 23, 1, 10, 10, 'rulers', 'Rulers and Accountability', 'Both passages emphasize the role of rulers in receiving God''s word. Acts 4:5 mentions ''rulers,'' while Isaiah 1:10 addresses ''rulers of Sodom,'' highlighting a theme of accountability among leaders.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 5, 33, 2, 1, 1, 'on the morrow', 'Morning Actions and Evil Plans', 'This connection highlights the theme of actions taken in the morning, as seen in both passages. In Acts 4:5, the rulers gather the next day, while Micah 2:1 speaks of those who practice evil when morning comes.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 5, 40, 27, 1, 2, 'rulers, and elders, and scribes', 'Connection of Rulers and Elders', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the rulers and elders in the events surrounding Jesus. In Acts, they are mentioned as part of the council, while in Matthew, they are depicted as conspiring against Jesus.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 5, 41, 15, 1, 1, 'rulers, and elders, and scribes', 'Council of Rulers and Elders', 'Both passages emphasize the involvement of rulers, elders, and scribes in significant judicial proceedings. This connection highlights the continuity of authority figures in the events surrounding Jesus'' trial and Peter''s defense.', 'parallel', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 5, 42, 20, 1, 1, 'rulers, and elders, and scribes', 'Connection of Rulers and Elders', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of rulers, elders, and scribes confronting Jesus. This connection highlights the ongoing opposition faced by Jesus from religious authorities.', 'parallel', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 5, 42, 22, 66, 66, 'elders, and scribes', 'Council of Rulers and Elders', 'This connection highlights the assembly of rulers, elders, and scribes in both passages. Both verses depict a formal gathering of these leaders to address significant matters.', 'parallel', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 6, 42, 3, 2, 2, NULL, 'Connection of High Priests', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of Annas and Caiaphas as high priests during significant events. This connection highlights their roles in the religious leadership at the time of John the Baptist and the apostles.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 6, 40, 26, 3, 3, NULL, 'High Priest Leadership Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the role of Caiaphas as a central figure among the high priests. The gatherings mentioned in each verse highlight the authority and influence of the high priestly family in Jerusalem during significant events.', 'parallel', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 6, 43, 18, 24, 24, 'Annas the high priest, and Caiaphas', 'Connection Between Annas and Caiaphas', 'Both passages emphasize the roles of Annas and Caiaphas in the trial of Jesus. Acts 4:6 mentions their gathering, while John 18:24 highlights Annas sending Jesus to Caiaphas.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 6, 43, 11, 49, 49, NULL, 'Connection of High Priests', 'This connection highlights the presence of Caiaphas, who is mentioned in both passages as a key figure among the high priests. Acts 4:6 lists Caiaphas alongside other high priests, while John 11:49 specifically identifies him as the high priest that year.', 'keyword', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 6, 43, 18, 13, 14, 'Annas the high priest, and Caiaphas', 'Connection of High Priests', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of Annas and Caiaphas in the context of Jesus'' trial. Acts 4:6 mentions Annas and Caiaphas together, while John 18:13-14 highlights their familial relationship and roles during Jesus'' arrest.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 7, 40, 21, 23, 23, 'by what power, or by what name', 'Authority and Power in Questioning', 'Both passages emphasize the questioning of authority and power. In Acts, the inquiry is about the power behind a miracle, while in Matthew, the focus is on the authority of Jesus'' actions in the temple.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 7, 41, 11, 28, 28, 'By what power, or by what name', 'Authority and Power Inquiry', 'Both passages emphasize questions about authority and power. In Acts, the inquiry is about the power behind a miracle, while in Mark, the focus is on the authority for Jesus'' actions.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 7, 44, 5, 40, 40, 'by what name', 'Authority in the Name of Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the authority of the name of Jesus. In Acts 4:7, the question of power and name is central, while Acts 5:40 shows the response to that authority by commanding the apostles not to speak in His name.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
